IMPORTANT: Lowest tilt KHNX runs into side of Sierra Nevada, so used a higher tilt, 2.4 degrees. This is a very high altitude tornado, but a deep, but weak mesocyclone on multiple tilts supports the idea that it is a supercell tornado nonetheless.
